  "uuid": "63a1d7e6a3b54d31a13ff72dc11e10bd",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Conservator/Curator Intern",
  "description": "<p><br></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conservaiton (cleaning, protection and display) of gallery objects.</li>\n  <li>Planning, organizing, and installing gallery exhibitions.</li>\n  <li>Support research and documentation for curatorial projects.</li>\n  <li>Conduct condition assessments and basic preventive conservation for artworks and objects.</li>\n  <li>Assist in cataloguing, labeling, and maintaining the collection database.</li>\n  <li>Contribute to marketing and educational activities such as exhibition texts, tours, or workshops.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Currently pursuing or recently completed studies in Art History, Museum Studies, Conservation, Fine Arts, or a related field.</li>\n  <li>Strong interest in curation, exhibition-making, and art conservation.</li>\n  <li>Excellent research, organization, and communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Detail-oriented with sensitivity to handling artworks and materials.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in MS Office; experience with collection databases or design software (e.g. Adobe Photoshop/InDesign) is a plus.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What You’ll Gain</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Mentorship from curatorial and conservation professionals.</li>\n  <li>Practical experience in exhibition management and preventive conservation.</li>\n  <li>Exposure to day-to-day operations of a working gallery or museum environment.</li>\n  <li>Opportunity to contribute to meaningful cultural and heritage projects.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>How to Apply</strong><br>\nPlease send your CV, a brief cover letter, and (if applicable) a writing sample or portfolio to <strong>admin@maek.com.sg </strong></p>",
